    "The propagation model from the l th layer to the ðl þ 1Þ th layer is as follows:",
    "where e A ¼ A þ I N, A is the adjacency matrix, I N is the identity matrix, e D is the degree matrix of nodes, H ðlÞ is the feature of the l th layer (H 0 ¼ M), W ðlÞ is the weight of the l th layer, σ is the nonlinear activation function.",
    "T and E represent two categories of the trait data for rice: the Trait (T) group and the Experiment (E) group.",
    "npj Systems Biology and Applications | (2024) 10:15",
